		"description": "<p>Most wizards don&rsquo;t bother with armor. You&rsquo;ve always doubted the wisdom of this practice, and further have never considered it a good idea to rely solely on your magical training when you could also learn to use weapons with a bit of practice. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your Strength, Dexterity, or Intelligence score increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</li>\n<li>You can use any weapon you are proficient with as a spellcasting focus for your wizard spells.</li>\n<li>You learn the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.nlto7z4j14ips45w]{Shield} spell if you do not already know it, or another wizard spell of the protection or weapon school if you do. When you cast it, you can choose to equip a mundane shield if you have a hand free as part of the casting of the spell (you may free your hands up by dropping a two-handed weapon if desired), but the AC bonus of the shield does not apply until the beginning of your next turn.</li>\n<li>After you cast a damaging spell, you can use your reaction to immediately make an Intelligence (Intimidation) check against a creature within 30 feet that witnessed the spell, opposed by the creature&rsquo;s Wisdom save. If the creature was damaged by the spell, you make the check with advantage. If you win the opposed check, the creature becomes frightened of you until the end of its next turn.</li>\n</ul>",
